{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c107503e-855b-48cc-8985-0ff6afa2403c","content":"With xUnit.net v3 + MTP, the VSTest filter syntax (`--filter`) is replaced by the `--filter` flag on the **MTP runner**, which uses a different expression language.\n\nYour old filter:\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~IntegrationTests&Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nBecomes:\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"/*[contains(@TestNodePath,'IntegrationTests')]/Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n\n| VSTest syntax | MTP syntax |\n|---|---|\n| `FullyQualifiedName~X` | `/*[contains(@TestNodePath,'X')]` |\n| `Category=Smoke` | Trait filtering via `/Category=Smoke` |\n| `&` (AND) | Combine as path predicates |\n\n**Or**, use the simpler flat form if you just need both conditions:\n```\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Smoke&/*[contains(@TestNodePath,'IntegrationTests')]\"\n```\n\n**Note:** xUnit v3 on MTP also supports the shorthand `--filter` with `=` for traits directly. The simplest equivalent is:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --treenode-filter \"/*[contains(@TestNodePath,'IntegrationTests')]/Category=Smoke\"\n```\n\nIf you'd prefer to keep the VSTest-compatible `--filter` syntax, add the VSTest bridge adapter (`Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge`) — but the recommended path forward with MTP is the tree-node filter syntax shown above.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"6bfc7422-c78f-4bbb-9474-2cffdeaeb8d8","outputTokens":369,"requestId":"BC2C:4B044:1B72518:1E8FCD2:69FA9163"},"id":"00448735-6a85-4d9d-84e4-b433ebb4a239","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:55:08.428Z","parentId":"7a07dc93-175a-4caa-91e3-caadd7bc21ab"}
